        <bioghist id="ref13">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Herb Lerner (1915-1972) was a Jewish Communist born in Lithuania, a soldier stationed during World War II in North Africa and Italy, and later the New Jersey director of the International Union of Mine, Mill, and Smelter Workers.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <userestrict id="ref16">
            <head>Use Restrictions</head>
            <p>Copyright (and related rights to publicity and privacy) to materials in this collection created by Herb Lerner are held by his second wife, Rosalie Harris-Lerner. Permission to publish or reproduce materials to which she holds copyright must be secured from the copyright holder. Please contact the Tamiment Library for assistance with contacting Rosalie Harris-Lerner.</p>
        </userestrict>
        <accessrestrict id="ref15">
            <head>Access Restrictions</head>
