        </prefercite>
        <acqinfo id="ref18">
            <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition note</head>
            <p>Donated by Roaslie Harris-Lerner, second wife of Herb Lerner, in 1997. The accession number associated with this gift is 2006.015.</p>
        </acqinfo>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The collection consists of hundreds of almost daily World War II letters (Aug 28, 1942-Sep 10, 1945) from Herb Lerner to his wife Ruth Lerner, also a Communist and an activist in the fur workers union (Joint Board, Fur, Leather &amp; Machine Workers Union). The letters contain domestic and international political commentary reflective of Lerner's Communist politics, and personal remarks, notably expressions of love and concern for his wife.</p>
        </scopecontent>
